", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 949}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked if she will be in LA in 2028, Storey said: \\\"I need to enjoy this one first but, to quote Simone Biles (Americangymnast), absolutely - never say never to anything.\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1120, \"end\": 1132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1051}, {\"ngram\": \"Storey\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"Americangymnast\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1149}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This just needs to sink in first because it was actually one of the most exciting races that we have had.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1301, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most exciting races\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1283}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the word go, it was full gas.\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1336, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the word\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"full gas\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1335}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My glutes are on fire.\", \"from\": 1338, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My glutes\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1348}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was creaking before the race, absolutely.\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1405, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1392}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that's normal and it's about finding ways to manage the process and the privilege of getting old as an athlete.\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1473}, {\"ngram\": \"the privilege\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1491}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1520}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wanted to be an athlete for as long as I possibly could.\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1582, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I never anticipated eight Games, let alone nine.\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1631, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"eight Games\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1614}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You put yourself out there every time you put yourself on the start line and I keep doing that and keep finding ways to win a bike race, so long may that continue.\\\"\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the start line\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1706}, {\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 1746, \"to\": 1750}, {\"ngram\": \"a bike race\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Former swimmer Storey was back in Clichy-sous-Bois in the eastern suburbs of the French capital two days on from complaining about the short distance of the 14.1km time trial after retaining the title in that event.\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 2015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clichy-sous-Bois\"}, {\"begin\": 1881, \"end\": 1887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.4854833689978722, \"rank\": 0.6459831455153338, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Former swimmer\", \"from\": 1800, \"to\": 1814}, {\"ngram\": \"Storey\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1821}, {\"ngram\": \"the eastern suburbs\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1873}, {\"ngram\": \"the short distance\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1949}, {\"ngram\": \"the 14.1km time trial\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"the title\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"that event\", \"from\": 2004, \"to\": 2014}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her second - and final - race of the Games was five laps of the same course - and the tightest Paralympic time trial she has contested.\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2152, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her second - and final - race\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2046}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2059}, {\"ngram\": \"five laps\", \"from\": 2064, \"to\": 2073}, {\"ngram\": \"the same course\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2092}, {\"ngram\": \"the tightest Paralympic time trial\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mother of two, watched by husband Barney and children Louisa and Charlie, was among the leading pack for the duration of the ride, alongside teenage runner-up Gaugain and Colombian bronze medallist Paula Ossa, before pulling away when it mattered most.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2192, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barney_Stinson\", \"score\": 0.9999999960768946, \"rank\": 3.7024206194846164e-09, \"text\": \"Barney\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barney_Stinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barney_Stinson\"}, {\"begin\": 2356, \"end\": 2361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paula_Hitler\", \"score\": 0.6576433443474443, \"rank\": 0.5205810390955113, \"text\": \"Paula\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paula_Hitler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paula_Hitler\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The mother\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2164}, {\"ngram\": \"children Louisa\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2218}, {\"ngram\": \"Charlie\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"the leading pack\", \"from\": 2242, \"to\": 2258}, {\"ngram\": \"the duration\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2275}, {\"ngram\": \"the ride\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2287}, {\"ngram\": \"teenage runner-up Gaugain and Colombian bronze medallist\", \"from\": 2299, \"to\": 2355}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's most successful Paralympian had just returned from Atlanta in 1996, having won the final three of her five swimming golds, when she was Gaugain's age.\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2412, \"end\": 2419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9586994140844068, \"rank\": 0.04285215112163609, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2438, \"end\": 2449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2473, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 0.9999997029272422, \"rank\": 2.9695450210790384e-07, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her five swimming golds\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2543}, {\"ngram\": \"Gaugain's age\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2571}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was thinking, 'you are up against a 19-year-old here', you remember what that was like, the nippiness of a 19-year-old,\\\" said Storey, who now has 30 Paralympic medals, including the record 19 golds, and holds a 100 per cent record on the bike.\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2820, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the nippiness\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2678}, {\"ngram\": \"Storey\", \"from\": 2703, \"to\": 2709}, {\"ngram\": \"30 Paralympic medals\", \"from\": 2723, \"to\": 2743}, {\"ngram\": \"the record 19 golds\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2774}, {\"ngram\": \"a 100 per cent record\", \"from\": 2786, \"to\": 2807}, {\"ngram\": \"the bike\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 2819}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am still nippy for a 46-year-old but I have to use it wisely.\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 2886, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I could see her furiously peddling feet but I threw my bike and it was mine \\\"It's amazing, really amazing.\", \"from\": 2888, \"to\": 2995, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"feet\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2927}, {\"ngram\": \"my bike\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 2947}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I am just delighted that my wheel was in front at the finish.\", \"from\": 2996, \"to\": 3057, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my wheel\", \"from\": 3021, \"to\": 3029}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 3037, \"to\": 3042}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 3046, \"to\": 3056}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The lap before a coach of hers (Gaugain) shouted from the other side of the road, 'next lap on the left', so I had a look where we were to make sure I was ready for that.\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3230, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The lap\", \"from\": 3060, \"to\": 3067}, {\"ngram\": \"a coach\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3082}, {\"ngram\": \"Gaugain\", \"from\": 3092, \"to\": 3099}, {\"ngram\": \"the other side\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3128}, {\"ngram\": \"the road\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3140}, {\"ngram\": \"next lap\", \"from\": 3143, \"to\": 3151}, {\"ngram\": \"the left\", \"from\": 3155, \"to\": 3163}, {\"ngram\": \"a look\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3181}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was a long way out but it was the only tactic she could use because I have the faster sprint.\", \"from\": 3232, \"to\": 3329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a long way\", \"from\": 3240, \"to\": 3250}, {\"ngram\": \"the only tactic\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3281}, {\"ngram\": \"the faster sprint\", \"from\": 3311, \"to\": 3328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"When we were together in that final corner, that's when I unleashed it.\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3403, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that final corner\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3374}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She tried to come again.\", \"from\": 3404, \"to\": 3428, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I could see her furiously peddling feet but I threw my bike and it was mine.\\\"\", \"from\": 3429, \"to\": 3506, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"feet\", \"from\": 3464, \"to\": 3468}, {\"ngram\": \"my bike\", \"from\": 3481, \"to\": 3488}, {\"ngram\": \"mine\", \"from\": 3500, \"to\": 3504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unwin and her pilot Jenny Holl edged Dunlevy and Linda Kelly by three seconds following a close battle over 99.4km to claim their second gold of the Games, with Fachie and Corrine Hall a minute and 35 seconds off the winning time of two hours, 37 minutes and 26 seconds.\", \"from\": 3508, \"to\": 3778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3508, \"end\": 3513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigel_Unwin\", \"score\": 0.820381670814942, \"rank\": 0.21894483454868888, \"text\": \"Unwin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigel_Unwin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nigel_Unwin\"}, {\"begin\": 3528, \"end\": 3538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Holl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Holl\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Holl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org